Hi. I'm running Debian testing, and had a very similar problem. I got a similar error when running `pip install caravel`. After the error, I did run, as you suggest

```
pip install cryptography
```

And I see how cryptography-1.1.4 is installed. But the weird thing is that if I run after that

```
pip install caravel
```

I see that cryptography-1.1.1 is installed once again:

```
(caravel)jgb@expisito:~/venvs$ pip install caravel
Requirement already satisfied (use --upgrade to upgrade): caravel in ./caravel/lib/python2.7/site-packages
Requirement already satisfied (use --upgrade to upgrade): babel==2.3.4 in ./caravel/lib/python2.7/site-packages (from caravel)
Downloading/unpacking cryptography==1.1.1 (from caravel)
  Downloading cryptography-1.1.1.tar.gz (348kB): 348kB downloaded
  Running setup.py (path:/tmp/pip-build-yqz2Om/cryptography/setup.py) egg_info for package cryptography
...
```

And then the same error again, after installing many packages...

Any idea?

The Caravel approach would be to precompute your data a pipeline and point Caravel to the output. We may support many-to-one joins in the future, but self-join seems like a slippery slope.

We are planning on adding a state of the art, integrated SQL editor to Caravel, so some of that more advanced SQL pre-processing could be done in that editor, and then visualized in Caravel.

If you are interested in retention, check out this super-informative video by an ex-Facebook colleague about "Growth Accounting":
https://www.facebook.com/video.php?v=3707283286197

I would add a bit to this. It's a little confusing that there are two query buttons - one top left and one top right. It would be simpler to only have one. Also, it may be worth not running the query on chart type change as too frequently the data is not set-up for the new chart type which leads to an error and you cannot fix that error without changing to another chart type. My suggestion would be to move query to the right of the chart type dropdown, make it a bold color and only show one query button. Also, only run query when the user clicks query not on chart type change as we don't re-run automatically when other inputs are changed.
